description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Registered Bank Nurse Opportunities&lt;/strong&gt; in various areas throughout Community Wards, Scheduled &amp; Unscheduled Care Divisions in all Hospital sites throughout the University Health Board.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are currently seeking to recruit highly motivated Registered Bank Nurses covering the full range of specialities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We care for our patients 7 days a week, 24 hours a day so you will need to have the flexibility to undertake shifts including nights and weekend working.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to exploring innovative ways of working to enhance patient experience. We know that our success depends on the commitment and dedication of our staff and we aim to recruit and retain the best staff possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We want Aneurin Bevan University Health Board to be an enjoyable and fulfilling place to work. We know that feeling valued at work has a positive impact on both staff and patients and our Values and Behaviours Framework highlights our commitment to this.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Is this you?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Can’t commit to a permanent job at present?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Family or other commitments prevent you working full time or to a set work pattern?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Want to keep up your professional skills?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Would like to gain experience in new areas?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Benefits of Working on the Bank:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible working hours&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pensionable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Weekly paid&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Development and Experience across a number of areas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Additional Annual Leave&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work available in a variety of different and interesting locations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are newly qualified or an experienced registered nurse and interested in joining the Resource bank, please complete the on-line application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 15 November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview date: 10 December 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameTracey RichJob titleAssistant Divisional NurseEmail addressTracey.rich@wales.nhs.ukTelephone number01633 238268&lt;/p&gt;
